0.1 How Do I Know What Geographies or Variables I Want?

https://walkerke.github.io/tidycensus/articles/basic-usage.html

v17 <- load_variables(2017, "acs5", cache = TRUE)

View(v17)

0.2 Call Libraries and Set Options

library(tidycensus) # get tidy data from the Census

library(tidyverse) # tidyverse including ggplot

options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE) # options

0.3 Census API Key

census_api_key("...") # Census API key

0.4 Get Data

Washtenaw <- get_acs(state = "MI", 
                     county = "Washtenaw", 
                     geography = "tract", 
                     variables = "B19013_001", 
                     geometry = TRUE)

0.6 Make a Map

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  scale_fill_viridis_c() # viridis colors

0.7 Try a Different Theme and Colors

https://github.com/gadenbuie/ggpomological

library(ggpomological)

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Greens") +
  theme_pomological_fancy()

0.8 ggthemes

https://jrnold.github.io/ggthemes/

0.8.1 WSJ

library(ggthemes)

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  theme_wsj() +
  theme(title = element_text(size = rel(.75)),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)),
        legend.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)))

0.8.2 Economist

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf() + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  theme_economist() +
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "greens",
                       direction = 1) +
  theme(title = element_text(size = rel(.75)),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)),
        legend.text = element_text(size = rel(.5)))

0.8.4 A Video Game Look With darkunica

library(ggthemes) 

Washtenaw %>% # data
  ggplot(aes(fill=estimate)) + # ggplot
  geom_sf(alpha=.75) + # geom for shapefiles
  labs(title = "Quick Map: Washtenaw County",
       subtitle = "Median Family Income") +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "green",
                      high = "darkgreen") + 
  theme_hc(bgcolor = "darkunica") +
  theme(title = element_text(size = rel(.75),
                             color = "green"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(.5),
                                 color = "green"),
        legend.text = element_text(size = rel(.5),
                                   color = "green"))
